  "- Form Submitted or Committed status and details are available on the Form collection.",
  "- Null‑safe proxy filter for forms: treat missing/null isProxy as non‑proxy; prefer $expr: { $ne: [\"$isProxy\", true] }.",
  "- When required to Search within Form associated with Activity Work Histories, search within its validatedForm.formData ",
  "- Search within forms (no AWH status filter):",
  "  • base_collection = \"forms\" (lowercase, NOT \"Form\").",
  "  • CRITICAL: Form.formData keys are UUIDs (field IDs), not field names. To search by field name, MUST $lookup FormTemplate first.",
  "  • Field-specific search by name: If user specifies a field name (e.g., 'PTW field checked', 'remarks field contains X'): (1) $lookup FormTemplate via formTemplateID; (2) $addFields matchingFieldIds = $map($filter(template.fields where field.label regex matches fieldName i), extract field.id); (3) $addFields fieldValues = $map(matchingFieldIds, get formData[$$fieldId]); (4) $match on fieldValues (for checkbox: check true/truthy; for text: regex match). Do NOT search formData keys directly.",
  "  • Text search in answers (no field name specified): flatten validatedForms.formData via $objectToArray → $map to string values using $cond/$type guards → $reduce/$concat to a single string → $expr $regexMatch (i).",
  "  • File name search: scan both Form.formData and templateSnapshot.fields[].files[].{ originalFileName, originalName, name } via flattening or a recursive $function.",
  "  • If also constrained by AWH status, start from ActivityWorkHistory (AWH‑first) and join Form; apply the form search on the joined rows only.",
  "  • Combined text + file search: Use $and to require both conditions; use $or if user says 'or'. Default to OR when ambiguous.",
  "  • Scope filters for form search: Apply vessel/schedule/date/tag filters BEFORE the text/file search. If vessel filter: join AWH via activityWorkHistoryID and filter AWH.vesselID. If date filter: join AWH and filter AWH.plannedDueDate or latest AWHE.performedOn. If tag filter: join FormTemplate and then SearchableTag.",
  "- When required to return the User details, join with User collection and return email. Never return phash.",
  "- Keep pipelines efficient and minimal; use joins only when needed.",
  // "- Absolutely non negotiable:Human-readable enrichment: When reporting foreign key IDs that map to display names/fields, join in the human-readable fields via pipeline $lookups when those collections/fields are present. If not present in `collections`, skip enrichment. Common enrichable fields include:",
  // "  • activityID → Activity.description",
