  // "- Non‑negotiable projection (activity/task/job): always project activity.description, maintenanceSchedule.shortName, vessel.vesselName, AWH._id, AWH.activityID, AWH.vesselID, AWH.committed, latest AWHE.performedOn as completionPerformedOn, and performedByUser.email.",
  // "  Use pipeline $lookup with $expr and the ID casting rule; $project these fields alongside the base fields. If a target collection/field is not present in 'collections', skip the enrichment."
  "- Defer human-readable enrichment:",
    "- Do not add $lookup stages solely to retrieve display names (e.g., Activity.description, Vessel.vesselName).",
  "",
  "- organizationID type by collection: PurchaseOrder, DocumentMetadata, Vendor, InventoryPart => ObjectId; ActivityWorkHistory => String. Choose the correct type in $match and joins.",
  "- AWH equipment grouping: For 'by machinery', $lookup Activity via activityID and group by Activity.machineryID; for schedule-level summaries, group by maintenanceScheduleID. After grouping, add { $match: { _id: { $ne: null } } } to drop null groups.",
  "- Derived downtime: downtimeHours is NOT stored. Always compute via $addFields: { downtimeHours: { $divide: [ { $subtract: [ '$downtimeEndDate', '$downtimeStartDate' ] }, 1000*60*60 ] } } before using in $match/$group/$project.",
  "- Projection safeguard: When later logic reads computed fields (e.g., total, onTime, onTimeRate, avgDuration), include them explicitly in a $project stage to avoid undefined references.",
  "- Operator selection: Dates → use $expr with $$NOW; for fixed calendar windows, prefer direct field ranges (index-friendly). Numbers → $gte/$lte. Text → case-insensitive $regex. References → $eq/$in with casting only on the variable side via $convert to 'objectId' when the target field is an ObjectId.",
  "- Intent templates (sketches):",
  "  • list_filtered: start with selective $match; optional $sort/$limit.",
  "  • count_by_group(field): $group { _id: '$<field>', count: { $sum: 1 } } → $sort { count: -1 }.",
  "  • top_k(by metric): compute metric in $addFields/$group → $sort desc → $limit K → $project keys + metric.",
  "  • trend_by_time(unit): $addFields t = $dateTrunc({ date: '$$NOW' | $<dateField>, unit: '<unit>', timezone: 'UTC' }) → $group by t → $sort by _id.",
  "  • calc_rate: $group numer/denom → $project { numer, denom, ratePct: { $multiply: [ { $divide: [ '$numer', '$denom' ] }, 100 ] } }.",
  "  • avg_duration / sum_duration: compute duration via $subtract (end-start); then $avg/$sum; never reference a non-existent stored duration.",
  "- DocumentMetadata certificates: base=DocumentMetadata; documentType is STRING. Dynamic field resolution:",
  "  • Certificate filtering: When intent is DMS/certificates, filter by regex /certificate/i on BOTH documentName AND documentType fields to ensure only certificate documents are included.",
  "  • Semantic field matching: Find DocumentType by typeName regex /certificate/i; find field where fieldType='date' AND (fieldLabel OR fieldName) contains 'expiry|expiration|valid|renewal|due' (case-insensitive); extract fieldName.",
  "  • Type casting (CRITICAL): customMetadata values can be String or Date. Always cast: $addFields tmpExpiry = { $convert: { input: \"$customMetadata.<fieldName>\", to: \"date\", onError: null, onNull: null } }; then $match { $expr: { $and: [{ $ne: [\"$tmpExpiry\", null] }, <date comparisons>] } }.",
  "  • $getField syntax (CRITICAL): When using $getField to access dynamic customMetadata fields, the 'field' parameter references the field containing the string value. CORRECT: { $getField: { field: \"$resolvedFieldName\", input: \"$customMetadata\" } }.",
  "  • $concat with $ anchor (CRITICAL): NEVER use standalone \"$\" string in $concat arrays - MongoDB interprets it as a field path causing '$' by itself is not a valid FieldPath error. For DocumentType matching, use simple equality: { $eq: [\"$typeName\", \"$$dmTypeName\"] } instead of building regex with $concat. Avoid dynamic regex construction with anchors.",
  "  • Multiple matches: prefer fields with 'expiry' > 'valid' > 'renewal' > 'due' in label.",
  "  • User-specified field: if normalized_request contains explicit field name, use it directly (skip semantic matching).",
  "  • Content search: when normalized_request includes filters.contentSearch, flatten customMetadata via $objectToArray + $reduce to concat all text values, then $regexMatch against documentName, description, and flattened text.",
  "  • For filename filters: join latest DocumentFile and use originalFileName.",
  "- Procurement metrics: On-time rate and average delivery days derive from expectedDeliveryDate vs actualDeliveryDate; ensure both are present when projecting results.",
  "- AWH null-safe booleans: isFailureEvent, isUnplannedMaintenance, hasDowntime can be null. For negations like 'not a failure' or 'planned maintenance': in regular $match use { $or: [ { field: false }, { field: null }, { field: { $exists: false } } ] }; inside $expr use { $or: [ { $eq: [\"$field\", false] }, { $eq: [{ $ifNull: [\"$field\", null] }, null] } ] }. For positive queries, require field === true.",
  "- AWH 'unplanned/ad‑hoc maintenance': Interpret strictly as isUnplannedMaintenance === true (positive check). Do NOT equate to maintenanceScheduleID == null. Use ActivityWorkHistory as base_collection. 'Across the fleet' => no vessel filter; 'all time' => no date filter.",

  "- DocumentMetadata expiry windows: After casting to tmpExpiry (date), define windows as — Expired: tmpExpiry < \"$$NOW\"; Valid now: tmpExpiry >= \"$$NOW\"; Expiring next N days: tmpExpiry >= \"$$NOW\" AND tmpExpiry < { \"$dateAdd\": { \"startDate\": \"$$NOW\", \"unit\": \"day\", \"amount\": N } }. Prefer an index-friendly direct range on tmpExpiry when bounds are constants.",
  "- AWH 'currently active downtime': Filter with hasDowntime === true AND use $expr: { $and: [ { $lte: [ \"$downtimeStartDate\", \"$$NOW\" ] }, { $or: [ { $eq: [ \"$downtimeEndDate\", null ] }, { $gt: [ \"$downtimeEndDate\", \"$$NOW\" ] } ] } ] }.",
  "- Downtime window clipping (sums/averages): For a window [START, END), compute clampedStart = { $max: [ \"$downtimeStartDate\", START ] }, clampedEnd = { $min: [ { $ifNull: [ \"$downtimeEndDate\", \"$$NOW\" ] }, END ] }; hours = { $divide: [ { $subtract: [ clampedEnd, clampedStart ] }, 1000*60*60 ] }. Ignore rows where { $not: { $gt: [ clampedEnd, clampedStart ] } }.",
  "- Procurement PO status semantics: Open/unfulfilled = ['draft','sent','acknowledged','partial_received']; Closed/fulfilled = ['completed']; Exclude 'cancelled' by default. 'Overdue POs' => expectedDeliveryDate < \"$$NOW\" AND status in Open.",
  "- Severity/impact synonyms: Map 'serious'/'high' to failureSeverity in ('major','critical') or operationalImpact in ('major','critical'); 'minor' maps to 'minor'. Apply case-insensitive matching.",
  "- Cross-category parts↔failures: To find parts ordered for failures, correlate AWH.relatedPartIDs and AWHE.partsUsed → MaintenancePartUsage.partID with PurchaseOrder.lineItems.partID. Use union logic: match if either set intersects. Prefer $lookup with $expr + $in; avoid Cartesian products.",


    "- Return raw foreign key IDs (e.g., activityID, machineryID, vesselID, formTemplateID, performedBy) and other fields required to compute results.",
    "- Absolutely non-negotiable:Projection ID key naming: In the final $project, rename each ID field to '<collectionName>_ID' using the owning/target collection name; e.g., vesselID => vessel_ID, latestEventID => ActivityWorkHistoryEvent_ID. Don't return \"_id\" by itself or any project an \"_id\" field without '<collectionName>_ID' suffix (latestEvent => AWHE_ID) .",
    "- Only use $lookup when strictly needed for filtering (e.g., matching by a name when ID is not provided); do not project the joined display fields unless filtering requires them.",
