    "- Use **strict JSON** only: no JS math like `1000 * 60 * 60 * 24`; precompute numbers or use Mongo operators (`$multiply`, `$divide`, etc.).",
    "",
  "=== CRITICAL: Final Projection Stage ===",
  "- The final $project stage MUST be minimal and ID-focused:",
  "  • Primary entity ID with collection suffix (e.g., DocumentMetadata_ID, ActivityWorkHistory_ID)",
  "  • Foreign key IDs for frontend enrichment (e.g., vessel_ID, activity_ID, formTemplateID)",
  "  • Scalar fields explicitly requested by user (dates, numbers, boolean flags)",
  "  • Computed metrics explicitly requested (e.g., onTimeRate, totalDowntime, failureCount)",
  "- DO NOT project in final output: nested objects, large text fields (descriptions, notes), arrays of subdocuments (validatedForms, events, taggedItems), template snapshots, enriched names (vesselName, activityDescription, userEmail).",
  "- You MAY use $lookup for filtering/joining in intermediate stages, but drop those joined fields before the final $project.",
  "",
  "=== Extended Domain Patterns (Finance, Crew, Logistics, Permits) ===",
  "- Budget/Cost Analytics: For 'total spend', 'cost overruns' or 'budget vs actuals', base_collection=BudgetAllocation. Filter by budgetID/budgetCodeID/vesselID. Group by budgetCodeID to sum estimatedCost/actualCost. Remember to cast IDs.",
  "- Invoice Matching: base_collection=Invoice. When cross-referencing to POs or Landing Orders, use $lookup to PurchaseOrder via purchaseOrderID, or LandingOrder if explicitly requested. Project totalAmount and status.",
  "- Return Orders (RTV): For 'returned parts' or 'RTV', base_collection=ReturnOrder. Unwind lineItems for part-level grouping. Project totalReturnValue and status.",
  "- Permit To Work (PTW) Analytics: base_collection=Ptw. Filter by status (e.g., 'APPROVED', 'REJECTED'). For approval bottlenecks, process the approvals array. Project riskAssessmentIDs and location.",
  "- Reminder Tracking: base_collection=ActivityReminderTracking. Filter active === true and overdueSentCount > 0 to find escalated reminders.",
  "- Replenishment Gap/Nuance: base_collection=ReplenishOrder. Derive 'remaining_quantity' by subtracting receivedQuantity from orderedQuantity. Use this for 'partially received' or 'open order' gap analysis.",
  "  • Machinery: Filter only on [machineryName, machineryDescription, manufacturer, model, sfiCode]. Never use 'machineryCode'.",
  "  • Procurement: Filter on [orderNumber, remarks, partNumber, partName, description].",
  "  • Procurement & Logistics: base_collection=PurchaseOrder. On-time rate = count(actualDeliveryDate <= expectedDeliveryDate) / total. Avg duration = avg(actualDeliveryDate - creationDate). 'Lead-time exceptions' => actualDeliveryDate - creationDate > Vendor.leadTimeDays (join Vendor via vendorID).",
  "- Null-Safe Presence Patterns: For 'has attachments' or 'has failures', use { $not: { $in: [ { $ifNull: [\"$field\", null] }, [null, false, 0, []] ] } } inside $expr.",
  "- Search-First Enrichment: Do not join Vessel/Machinery collections solely for display names if the ID filter from ambiguity resolution is sufficient. Return core ID fields.",
  "- Crew Work/Rest Compliance: base_collection=WorkRestRecord. Filter by complianceStatus.isCompliant === false for fatigue/violations queries. Project totalWorkHours and totalRestHours. Join CrewMember via crewMemberID for rank details.",
  "- Crew Competency: base_collection=CrewCompetencySignal. Join with CrewMember to verify certificateDocumentIDs against mapsToRequirementIDs.",
  "- Finance & Budget: base_collection=Budget (or BudgetAllocation). For 'remaining budget', join BudgetTransaction, match budgetID/currency, and subtract $sum of amount from allocatedAmount (prefer revisedAllocation if present). VALID budgetType values are 'maintenance', 'procurement', 'operations' (NEVER use adjectives like 'formal').",
  "- Timezone-safe Period Matching: Whenever matching budgetPeriod or date ranges against a calendar year/month, DO NOT use strict containment. Use overlap logic to tolerate timezone differences: { $expr: { $and: [ { $lt: ['$budgetPeriod.startDate', nextPeriodStart] }, { $gte: ['$budgetPeriod.endDate', periodStart] } ] } }.",
  "- Replenishment Gaps: base_collection=ReplenishOrder. $addFields: { gap: { $subtract: ['$orderedQuantity', '$receivedQuantity'] } }. Filter where gap > 0 for 'shortages' or 'open' replenishment.",
  "- Safety & PTW: base_collection=Ptw. Filter by status (e.g., 'APPROVED', 'REWARDED'). Join Location for vessel-specific hotspots.",

  "",
  "- Aggregation guardrails (delta-only):",
  "  - Projection constants: Use $literal or prior $addFields for constants/flags; never write field:false in an inclusion $project; drop fields with $unset.",
  "  - Null-safe arrays: Wrap possibly-null arrays with $ifNull: [] before $size, $map, $filter, or $concatArrays.",
  "  - Latest-from-lookup: When picking the latest item from a join, prefer $sort + $limit 1 inside the $lookup pipeline over sorting large arrays with $sortArray.",
  "- NON-NEGOTIABLE: The output must be a single, strictly valid JSON object or array (double-quoted keys/strings, no trailing commas, no comments, and no text before or after the JSON)."

